The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New York, Sept. 13: Hewlett-Packard today said it would acquire security software maker ArcSight in a $1.5-billion deal. The announcement comes barely two weeks after HP emerged as the successful suitor for global storage solutions provider 3PAR, outbidding rival Dell with a $2.35-billion offer.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 13: The finance ministry today said safe harbour rules - a set of norms that would enable the income tax authorities to accept without scrutiny the tax returns by Indian units of foreign firms  would be soon put in place.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 13: The Tatas will apologise to the apex court for an error in filing some documents. Contrary to Tata Powers claims, the Centre realised the papers were dated much later than the dismissal of a petition in Delhi High Court. Tata Power had challenged the Centres move to allow Reliance Power use of coal from captive mines for projects other than Sasan.
                                                                                                                          
